  "text": "Interestingly some antisense tags were identified as differentially expressed in response to androgen. Antisense to NKX3-1 is of particular note. Transcription of this gene is (Continued) enhancer region [CITATION_1] . Anti-sense RNA is involved in transcriptional silencing of sense transcript, imprinting control, post-transcriptional down-regulation of sense transcript or even stabilizing/promotion of the expression of the sense transcript [CITATION_2] . In the case of NKX3-1, antisense transcript may be a negative feedback mechanism; however, this remains to be determined.",
